<h2><a name="do" id="do">do</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="kw1">do</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
    statement<span class="sy0">-</span>list;
    <span class="br0">&#125;</span> <span class="kw1">while</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> condition <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

The do construct evaluates the given statement-list repeatedly, until condition
becomes false. Note that every do loop will evaluate its statement list at
least once, because the terminating condition is tested at the end of the loop.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="break" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:break">break</a>, <a href="continue" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:continue">continue</a>, <a href="for" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:for">for</a>, <a href="while" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:while">while</a>
</p>

</div>
